<br>
the key is destroyed when it is used.<br>
<br>
when you die your body can be ressed inside, its when the time expires that it is moved outside to the exit point.<br>
<br>
Just responding to Rog's post that there NEVER will be end game content for non-guilded people.<br>
<br>
Its just the way the game was designed for better or for worse. I look at quests such as the Sheild of Bane Warding and the Cloak of Truth and see items where the bottleneck is the time consumed in the quest rather than the boss mob. Now if those items were no drop they would have been perfect content.<br>
It amazes me sometimes how much thought goes into EQ content and how many bad decisions are made. From listening to the designers at the fan fare it seems to me that the root of the problem rests with to many changes in the guard on the design team, lack of agreement in their groups and the pressure from full time gamers over casual gamers is much greater.<br>
I will never forget seeing some guy from Afterlife and thinking to myself... that was exactly how I pictured him. This games high end content is designed for large guilds who's players play 40+ hrs a week. Thank god the rest of us have the RTA so we can plan out a Sat event in places like Fear and Hate and have some hope of actually having something worth killing. <p><p>
