<br>
<br>
This thread isn't even a Ragefire specific thread , but it seems to come up quite a lot .... <br>
<br>
<br>
Just in regards to the whole AFK while at Ragefire , because people do it all the time in the bazaar, thus making the need to hand out UN/PASS a moot point, I make this point , and I'd be willing to bet that I'm not the only person in this boat. <br>
<br>
Currently as things stand with the &quot;RageFire Etiquette&quot; , I have no chance of getting my Epic ever , without giving out my UN/PASS . <br>
<br>
If/when I get chardok done, and make the move to skyfire , that is where my Epic ends. For a couple of reasons. <br>
<br>
A) What is considered a reasonable amount of time to return from LD ?  This is not specified , its just one of those things. <br>
For some people this could be 15 minutes , for others it could be 30 minutes. <br>
<br>
B) Once Ragefire spawns, you have 12 hours to kill him.<br>
<br>
Both of these facts completely eliminate me from the chance of EVER getting my epic without giving out my Characters UN/PASS and setting up a rotation with the character so that someone is always watching. <br>
<br>
I work a 10 hour shift at work , and I live 45 minutes away from work ,on a good day with no traffic. This means that I'm out of the house for 12 - 13 hours at a time , maybe more pending traffic on the way home , since that is rush hour. <br>
<br>
How does this play into this? It means that should I go LD while at work , while I am AFK . There is no way for me to know this , and there is no way for me to Log the Character back on .  So whatever may be considered a &quot; Reasonable amount of time for LD's &quot; doesn't include everyone. <br>
<br>
Then again , Should ragefire spawn while I'm at work, I have 12 hours to kill him , hmmm , again same thing , if I'm at work , there is absolutely nothing that I can do about this , and it is quite possible , that by the time I get home , my '12 hour ' time limit will either be up , or there won't be enough time to muster a force. <br>
<br>
<br>
Yes I have 3 days off , however usually I can't devote all 3 of these days to camping Rage ... I can come close sometimes but not quite.  <br>
<br>
I am also looking at the odds , that most likely Rage would spawn while I'm at work , due to the fact that work is 4 days of my week , and thats all those 4 days are. <br>
<br>
And the whole Idea of taking Vacation for this , is not Feasable , as there is no way to know when my week for Ragefire would be , due to the AFK / LD point up above. <br>
<br>
So Unfortunately Rog , in this Case , AFK is not my friend . <br>
<br>
And there is no Hypothetical here .... I'm not even the person that made the Original Post about the Hypothetical Cleric , but we do exist.... <br>
<br>
I am a 55 Cleric<br>
I am NOT TAGGED<br>
<br>
And while I won't claim that I don't have any friends on the rathe **If I could make that claim , I wouldn't be playing on the rathe** , I can say , that the majority of my friends , either have different days off than I do , or they work Day shift / afternoon shift .  Thus the most of my friends that are on at any given point in time , is somewhere around 5 - 6 people , which is no where near the amount of people needed to do Rage. <br>
<br>
So its not just a Hypothetical ... There are those out there , that this is the case... <br>
<br>
Yes I could go Guild Searching , but you know what there aren't that many guilds out there that I am even remotely interested in. For those few guilds that I would be interested in pursuing a tag , there is some Pre - Req for joining the Guild that I don't make...Or the Guild in general , when the majority of there players are on , play at a completely different time frame then when I am on .  <br>
<br>
I may eventually re - tag , with who I don't know, but I don't believe that it is right to state that Epics are only for those that are in guilds. And that is what it is looking like here...<br>
<br>
/rant off <br>
<br>
<br>
Don't go counting that Hypotheticals are just that .... <br>
<br>
